title: The Dennis Prager Radio Show JAN-06-2014 MON
description:
The Dennis Prager Radio Show JAN-06-2014 MON.......PODCAST




Dennis Prager Radio Show
Prager 20140106  3 The Thrill of Victory

Prager H3: It was thrilling weekend for San Francisco and Indianapolis football fans,
            and depressing one for Green Bay and Kansas City fans.
              Life is a seldom a series of victories.
                 Sports can teach that lesson

      The media has barely covered the unintentionally funny story of the global warming
          research ship stuck in Antarctic ice

      Dennis talks to Max Boot, senior fellow at Council on Foreign Relations,
         about the dire situation in Iraq.





Prager 20140106  2 Teens and 9/11

Prager H2: Dennis wonders what teens are taught about 9/11.
             Has the story become a victim of political correctness
                 like so much in American education?

      Rolling Stone magazine features an economic prescription for America .. pure Marxism 

        Humanities departments are abandoning the humanities

      Dennis talks to Adrian Levy, investigative journalist based in SE Asia.
                   His new book is The Siege: 68 Hours Inside the Taj Hotel.


Prager 20140106  1 Cold, Colder, Coldest

Prager H1: Record cold grips Chicago and the entire Midwest.
               Maybe a little Global Warming would be a good thing.
                  Ask somebody from the Windy City or Minneapolis what they think

       The anti-smoking crowd goes after e-cigarettes even though e-cigarettes help people to stop smoking


     A great power vacuum has been created in the Mideast because a great power has left the Mideast
